Install Tools (Step-by-Step)
1. Install Oracle VirtualBox

Download from Oracle VirtualBox Downloads

Install VirtualBox on your Windows machine.

Create a new VM:

OS: Ubuntu 20.04 (ISO can be downloaded from Ubuntu
)

RAM: 6GB (minimum)

CPU: 4 vCPU

Storage: 50GB dynamically allocated

Start VM and install Ubuntu.

ðŸ’¡ Why VM?
Most tools (Magic, OpenLANE, Yosys) are Linux-native and may not run properly on Windows. Using a VM ensures smooth installation and a reproducible environment.

2. Install Tools on Ubuntu

After Ubuntu is running, open Terminal and follow steps:

(a) Yosys
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install make build-essential clang bison flex \
libreadline-dev gawk tcl-dev libffi-dev git \
graphviz xdot pkg-config python3 libboost-system-dev \
libboost-python-dev libboost-filesystem-dev zlib1g-dev -y

git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys.git
cd yosys
make config-gcc
make
sudo make install

(b) Icarus Verilog
sudo apt-get install iverilog -y

(c) GTKWave
sudo apt install gtkwave -y

(d) Ngspice
# Download latest version from https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/
tar -zxvf ngspice-37.tar.gz
cd ngspice-37
mkdir release
cd release
../configure  --with-x --with-readline=yes --disable-debug
make
sudo make install

(e) Magic
sudo apt-get install m4 tcsh csh libx11-dev tcl-dev tk-dev libcairo2-dev \
mesa-common-dev libglu1-mesa-dev libncurses-dev -y

git clone https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/magic
cd magic
./configure
make
sudo make install

(f) OpenLANE
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y build-essential python3 python3-venv python3-pip make git \
apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common

curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io -y
sudo docker run hello-world

sudo groupadd docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
sudo reboot


After reboot:

docker run hello-world
git --version
docker --version
python3 --version
python3 -m pip --version
make --version
python3 -m venv -h


Then install OpenLANE:

cd $HOME
git clone https://github.com/The-OpenROAD-Project/OpenLane
cd OpenLane
make
make test

3. Take Screenshots

After successful installation of each tool, run the version command:

yosys --version
iverilog -V
gtkwave --version
magic --version
docker --version


Take screenshots and save them in your repo under a folder Tool-Installation-Snapshots/.

4. Update GitHub Repo

Add a file Installation-Guide.md in your repo and document:

Steps followed

Issues faced (if any)

Screenshots of successful installation

Commit and push the changes.
